page.title: 06Land mammals on Lundy.
page.content: {Soay Sheep}roam around Lundy freely especially on the north east side. Sometimes they are culled to keep numbers down. { {Rats.}There are Black and Brown rats. Black rats are supposed to have a colony on Rat Island. { {Rabbits}live all over the place. Puffins sometimes take over their old burrows. Most of them are grey .There seemed to be more rabbit warrens at the south of the island. { {Silka deer}roam freely around the east of the island (the lee side) mostly in the rhododendrons.{ { { Russell and Alex Watkins. {}
